item.description:
The project Considering a set of points p_i, 1&lt;i&lt;n, and a limit distance s, we want to know the number a connex component. Two vertices p_i and p_j are linked by an edge if d(p_i, p_j) &lt;= s.
A connex component is a sub-graph where all the vertices are linked by transitivity.
A solution I worked in pair with ELHAJ-LAHSEN Hugo on different methods. We studied quadtrees, M-trees, VP-trees, Divide-and-conquer algorithm, optimization &hellip;
